org.jcvi.jillion.trace.fastq

Interface FastqParser

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BfqFileParser, FastqFileParser

    public interface FastqParser
    FastqParser is an interface that will parse a FASTQ formatted structure and call the appropriate visit methods on the given FastqVisitor.
    Author:
    dkatzel

    • Method Detail

      • canParse

        boolean canParse()
        Can this handler accept new parse requests via parse() calls. Some implementations of FastqParser may only allow one parse call in its lifetime (for example, if the fastq structure is being parsed via an InputStream).
        Returns:
        true if this handler can handle new parse requests; false otherwise.

      • canCreateMemento

        boolean canCreateMemento()
        Is this FastqParser's callbacks capable of creating FastqVisitor.FastqVisitorCallback.FastqVisitorMementos.
        Returns:
        true if this callback can create mementos; false otherwise.

      • isReadOnceOnly

        boolean isReadOnceOnly()
        Can the parse(FastqVisitor) or #parse(FastqVisitor, FastqVisitorMemento) methods be called multiple times. Some implementations are working off of an InputStream that can't be rewound or reset we can only read Once.
        Returns:
        true if the data can only be parsed once; false otherwise.

      • parse

        void parse(FastqVisitor visitor)
    throws IOException
        Parse the fastq structure starting from the beginning and call the appropriate visit methods on the given FastqVisitor.
        Parameters:
        visitor - the FastqVisitor instance to call visit methods on; can not be null;
        Throws:
        IOException - if there is a problem parsing the fastq.
        NullPointerException - if visitor is null.
        IllegalStateException - if this handler can not accept any new parse requests.
        See Also:
        canParse()

      • parse

        void parse(FastqVisitor visitor,
           FastqVisitor.FastqVisitorCallback.FastqVisitorMemento memento)
    throws IOException
        Parse the fastq structure starting from location provided by the FastqVisitor.FastqVisitorCallback.FastqVisitorMemento and call the appropriate visit methods on the given FastqVisitor.
        Parameters:
        visitor - the FastqVisitor instance to call visit methods on; can not be null;
        memento - the FastqVisitor.FastqVisitorCallback.FastqVisitorMemento instance to tell the parser where to start parsing from; can not be null.
        Throws:
        IOException - if there is a problem parsing the fastq file.
        NullPointerException - if either the visitor or memento are null.
        UnsupportedOperationException - if mementos are not supported by this parser implementation (for example when parsing an InputStream instead of a File).
        IllegalStateException - if this handler can not accept any new parse requests.
        See Also:
        canParse()

      • getFile

        Optional<File> getFile()
        Get the Fastq encoded file being parsed.
        Returns:
        An Optional File if it is known.
        Since:
        5.2
